07/07/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu will make a three-day official visit to the United States beginning on 26 July, his office announced on Thursday (6 July). 
In addition to US counterpart George W. 
Bush, Basescu is scheduled to meet with Defence Secretary Donald Rumsfeld and members of congress. 
The visit is aimed at strengthening bilateral co-operation, particularly in the fields of information technology, infrastructure and energy. 
The talks also will focus on Romania's contribution to NATO missions. 
(Rompres - 06/07/06)
